  "text": "The Firefox Content Security Policy enforcement infrastructure is implemented across several key files in the dom/security/ directory:\n\n**CSP Directive Parsing:**\nThe nsCSPParser class (dom/security/nsCSPParser.h/.cpp) is the primary CSP directive parser. It implements the static method parseContentSecurityPolicy() which tokenizes and parses CSP policy strings according to the W3C CSP specification. The parser is a state machine that processes directives and source lists.\n\n**CSP Context and Policy Management:**\nThe nsCSPContext class (dom/security/nsCSPContext.h/.cpp) implements the main CSP context that holds multiple policies and handles CSP enforcement. It includes methods like GetAllowsInline() which specifically evaluates script-src and style-src directives for inline scripts/styles by checking nonces, hashes, and the 'unsafe-inline' keyword. The class implements the nsIContentSecurityPolicy XPCOM interface and handles violation reporting.\n\n**CSP Utilities and Violations:**\nThe nsCSPUtils.h/.cpp files define the CSP infrastructure including the nsCSPPolicy class that represents a parsed policy with directives, and various source classes (nsCSPSchemeSrc, nsCSPHostSrc, nsCSPKeywordSrc, nsCSPNonceSrc, nsCSPHashSrc, etc.). These utilities also handle violation reporting through functions like CSP_LogLocalizedStr() and CSP_LogMessage().\n\n**XPCOM Interface:**\nThe nsIContentSecurityPolicy XPCOM interface (dom/interfaces/security/nsIContentSecurityPolicy.idl) defines the scriptable interface for CSP operations, including constants for CSP directives (SCRIPT_SRC_DIRECTIVE, SCRIPT_SRC_ELEM_DIRECTIVE, SCRIPT_SRC_ATTR_DIRECTIVE) and methods for policy access and checking.\n\n**Inline Script Evaluation:**\nInline script-src enforcement is implemented in nsCSPContext::GetAllowsInline() method, which checks if inline scripts are allowed by evaluating nonces (for <script nonce=\"...\">), hashes of script content, and keywords like 'unsafe-inline' and 'strict-dynamic'. It also handles violation reporting when inline scripts are blocked.\n\n**JavaScript Eval Checking:**\nThe CSPEvalChecker class (dom/security/CSPEvalChecker.h/.cpp) provides static methods CheckForWindow() and CheckForWorker() that intercept and check eval() calls against the CSP unsafe-eval directive, blocking eval if not permitted.\n\n**Supporting Files:**\nnsCSPService.cpp/.h implements the CSPService XPCOM service that acts as a content policy for checking CSP restrictions on various content loads."
}

